{"type":"message","id":"dc10ed3a","parentId":"f51e5f62","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:01:08.017Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"仍然是404错误。看来tushare的API确实无法访问。这可能是：\n\n1. 网络问题：防火墙或代理阻止\n2. tushare的API endpoint可能有问题\n3. 或者请求的方式不对\n\n让我检查一下tushare的文档，看看是否有其他方式，或者是否有其他的接口。\n\n另外，也可以尝试使用efinance（东方财富的另一个Python包）或baostock（百度的包）。\n\n但现在的核心问题是：数据源都无法访问（akshare代理问题，tushare 404错误）。\n\n既然用户只是说\"简单 tushare 测试脚本\"，我应该给用户一个明确的状态总结和建议。\n\n不过，让我先尝试检查是否能在浏览器中打开tushare网站，看看是不是网站本身的问题。\n\n或者，我可以尝试卸载并重新安装tushare，看看是否有帮助。\n\n但更重要的是，我应该给用户一个清晰的行动方案。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## 🔍 诊断结果：tushare API 无法访问\n\n**错误信息**：`HTTP Error 404: Not Found`\n\n### 问题分析\n\n| 可能原因 | 可能性 | 说明 |\n|----------|--------|------|\n| **1. 网络问题** | ⚠️⚠️⚠️ 高 | 防火墙/代理阻止访问 |\n| **2. tushare API 故障** | ⚠️⚠️ 中 | 服务器暂时不可用 |\n| **3. tushare 版本过旧** | ⚠️ 低 | 当前版本：1.4.25 |\n| **4. Python 环境问题** | ⚠️ 低 | urllib 库版本不兼容 |\n\n---\n\n## 💡 立即可用的替代方案\n\n### 方案1：使用浏览器测试 tushare（推荐）\n\n**手动测试步骤**：\n1. 在浏览器打开：https://tushare.pro/\n2. 登录你的账号\n3. 点击\"个人中心\" → 查看 \"API Token\"\n4. 如果能正常访问，说明是 Python 网络问题\n5. 如果打不开，说明是系统网络问题\n\n---\n\n### 方案2：尝试其他 A股数据源"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_702f7f70ae58409988047206","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\"\"\"\n使用本地 CSV 数据进行模拟扫描\n（作为 akshare/tushare 无法使用时的备用方案）\n\"\"\"\n\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nimport os\n\n# =================== Configuration ===================\n\nTOTAL_CAPITAL = 50000\nSINGLE_STOCK_MAX_RATIO = 0.20\nTOTAL_MAX_POSITION = 0.80\nTAKE_PROFIT_RATIO = 0.15\nSTOP_LOSS_RATIO = 0.05\nMA5_PERIOD = 5\nMA10_PERIOD = 10\nVOLUME_MULTIPLIER = 1.5\nRSI_MAX = 70\n\n# Position file\nPOSITION_FILE = \"quant_positions_local.json\"\nSCAN_RESULT_FILE = \"scan_results_local.csv\"\n\n# =================== Core Classes ===================\n\nclass LocalDataStrategy:\n    \"\"\"Local data strategy (simulated)\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.positions = {}\n        self.load_positions()\n\n    def calculate_rsi(self, prices, period=14):\n        \"\"\"Calculate RSI\"\"\"\n        delta = prices.diff()\n        gain = (delta.where(delta > 0, 0)).rolling(window=period).mean()\n        loss = (-delta.where(delta < 0, 0)).rolling(window=period).mean()\n        rs = gain / loss\n        rsi = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))\n        return rsi\n\n    def check_buy_signal(self, df):\n        \"\"\"Check buy conditions\"\"\"\n        if df is None or len(df) < 10:\n            return False, \"Not enough data\"\n\n        latest = df.iloc[-1]\n        prev = df.iloc[-2]\n\n        # 1. Golden cross check\n        ma5_golden = (prev['ma5'] < prev['ma10']) and (latest['ma5'] > latest['ma10'])\n\n        if not ma5_golden:\n            return False, \"No golden cross\"\n\n        # 2. Volume check\n        vol_ratio = latest['volume'] / latest['avg_volume']\n        if vol_ratio < VOLUME_MULTIPLIER:\n            return False, f\"Volume too low ({vol_ratio:.2f} < {VOLUME_MULTIPLIER})\"\n\n        # 3. RSI check\n        rsi_ok = not pd.isna(latest['rsi']) and latest['rsi'] < RSI_MAX\n        if not rsi_ok:\n            return False, f\"RSI too high ({latest['rsi']:.2f} >= 70)\"\n\n        return True, f\"All conditions met: MA5={latest['ma5']:.2f} > MA10={latest['ma10']:.2f}, RSI={latest['rsi']:.2f}, VolumeRatio={vol_ratio:.2f}\"\n\n    def create_sample_data(self):\n        \"\"\"Create sample stock data for testing\"\"\"\n        print(\"\\n[1] Creating sample stock data...\")\n\n        # Simulate 20 stocks\n        stocks = []\n        for i in range(20):\n            code = f\"600{50001 + i:05d}\"\n            name = f\"模拟公司{i:02d}\"\n\n            # Generate price data (60 days)\n            dates = pd.date_range(\n                start=datetime.now() - timedelta(days=60),\n                periods=60,\n                freq='D'\n            )\n\n            import numpy as np\n\n            # Random walk for prices\n            base_price = np.random.uniform(5, 100)\n            returns = np.random.normal(0.02, 0.03, 60)\n            prices = [base_price]\n            for ret in returns:\n                prices.append(prices[-1] * (1 + ret))\n\n            # Generate volumes\n            volumes = [np.random.randint(10000000, 100000000) for _ in range(60)]\n\n            df = pd.DataFrame({\n                'date': dates,\n                'open': [p * (1 + np.random.uniform(-0.02, 0.02)) for p in prices],\n                'close': prices,\n                'volume': volumes\n            })\n\n            # Calculate indicators\n            df['ma5'] = df['close'].rolling(window=MA5_PERIOD).mean()\n            df['ma10'] = df['close'].rolling(window=MA10_PERIOD).mean()\n            df['avg_volume'] = df['volume'].rolling(window=20).mean()\n            df['volume_ratio'] = df['volume'] / df['avg_volume']\n            df['rsi'] = self.calculate_rsi(df['close'])\n\n            # Check if latest day has golden cross\n            if len(df) >= 10:\n                latest = df.iloc[-1]\n                prev = df.iloc[-2]\n                df['golden_cross'] = (prev['ma5'] < prev['ma10']) and (latest['ma5'] > latest['ma10'])\n\n            stocks.append({\n                'code': code,\n                'name': name,\n                'data': df\n            })\n\n        print(f\"Created {len(stocks)} sample stocks\")\n\n        return stocks\n\n    def scan_stocks(self, max_results=20):\n        \"\"\"Scan stocks for buy signals\"\"\"\n        print(\"\\n[2] Scanning stocks for buy signals...\")\n        print(f\"Max results: {max_results}\")\n\n        stocks = self.create_sample_data()\n        candidates = []\n\n        for stock in stocks:\n            code = stock['code']\n            name = stock['name']\n            df = stock['data']\n\n            # Check buy conditions\n            is_signal, reason = self.check_buy_signal(df)\n\n            if is_signal:\n                latest = df.iloc[-1]\n                candidates.append({\n                    'code': code,\n                    'name': name,\n                    'close': latest['close'],\n                    'change': (latest['close'] - latest['open']) / latest['open'] * 100,\n                    'ma5': latest['ma5'],\n                    'ma10': latest['ma10'],\n                    'volume_ratio': latest['volume_ratio'],\n                    'rsi': latest['rsi'],\n                    'signal_reason': reason,\n                    'scan_time': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\n                })\n\n            if len(candidates) >= max_results:\n                print(f\"\\nFound {max_results} candidates, stopping scan\")\n                break\n\n        print(f\"\\nScan complete! Found {len(candidates)} candidates\")\n\n        return candidates\n\n    def save_scan_results(self, candidates):\n        \"\"\"Save scan results\"\"\"\n        df = pd.DataFrame(candidates)\n        df.to_csv(SCAN_RESULT_FILE, index=False, encoding='utf-8-sig')\n        print(f\"\\nScan results saved to: {SCAN_RESULT_FILE}\")\n\n        # Also save JSON\n        import json\n        with open('scan_results_local.json', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            json.dump(candidates, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n\n        return df\n\n    def load_positions(self):\n        \"\"\"Load positions\"\"\"\n        import json\n        if os.path.exists(POSITION_FILE):\n            with open(POSITION_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                self.positions = json.load(f)\n\n    def save_positions(self):\n        \"\"\"Save positions\"\"\"\n        import json\n        with open(POSITION_FILE, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            json.dump(self.positions, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n\n    def add_position(self, stock_code, name, price, shares):\n        \"\"\"Add position\"\"\"\n        self.positions[stock_code] = {\n            'name': name,\n            'cost': price,\n            'shares': shares,\n            'date': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d'),\n            'stop_loss': price * (1 - STOP_LOSS_RATIO),\n            'take_profit': price * (1 + TAKE_PROFIT_RATIO)\n        }\n        self.save_positions()\n\n    def print_dashboard(self):\n        \"\"\"Print position dashboard\"\"\"\n        print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*80)\n        print(\"A-Share Quant Trading - Position Dashboard (Local Data Version)\")\n        print(\"=\"*80)\n\n        used_capital = sum([pos['cost'] * pos['shares'] for pos in self.positions.values()])\n        self.cash = TOTAL_CAPITAL - used_capital\n\n        print(f\"\\n[Capital Overview]\")\n        print(f\"Total Capital: {TOTAL_CAPITAL:,.2f} Yuan\")\n        print(f\"Position Value: {used_capital:,.2f} Yuan\")\n        print(f\"Cash Balance: {self.cash:,.2f} Yuan\")\n        print(f\"Position Ratio: {(used_capital/TOTAL_CAPITAL*100):.2f}%\")\n\n        print(f\"\\n[Position Details]({len(self.positions)} stocks)\")\n        print(f\"{'Code':<10} {'Name':<15} {'Shares':<10} {'Cost':<10} {'Price':<10} {'Profit':<12} {'Profit%':<10}\")\n        print(\"-\"*80)\n\n        for code, pos in self.positions.items():\n            # Simulate current price (for demo, use cost +/- random)\n            import numpy as np\n            price_change = np.random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05)\n            current_price = pos['cost'] * (1 + price_change)\n\n            profit = (current_price - pos['cost']) * pos['shares']\n            profit_ratio = profit / (pos['cost'] * pos['shares']) * 100\n\n            sign = \"+\" if profit >= 0 else \"\"\n            print(f\"{code:<10} {pos['name']:<15} {pos['shares']:<10} {pos['cost']:<10.2f} {current_price:<10.2f} {sign}{profit:.2f} {profit_ratio:>7.2f}%\")\n\n        position_ratio = (used_capital / TOTAL_CAPITAL * 100) if TOTAL_CAPITAL > 0 else 0\n        print(f\"\\n[Risk Control Status]\")\n        if position_ratio > TOTAL_MAX_POSITION * 100:\n            print(f\"WARNING: Position ratio too high ({position_ratio:.2f}% > {TOTAL_MAX_POSITION*100:.0f}%)\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"OK: Position ratio normal ({position_ratio:.2f}%)\")\n\n        print(\"=\"*80)\n\n# =================== Main Function ===================\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main function\"\"\"\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n    print(\"A-Share Quant Trading - Local Data Version (Demo)\")\n    print(\"=\"*60)\n\n    strategy = LocalDataStrategy()\n\n    # Print position dashboard\n    strategy.print_dashboard()\n\n    # If command line arg is 'scan', then execute scanning\n    import sys\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1 and sys.argv[1] == 'scan':\n        print(\"\\nStarting stock scanning (using simulated data)...\")\n        candidates = strategy.scan_stocks(max_results=20)\n        strategy.save_scan_results(candidates)\n\n        # Display candidate stocks\n        if candidates:\n            print(\"\\n[Candidate Stock List]\")\n            print(f\"{'Code':<10} {'Name':<15} {'Price':<10} {'Change%':<10} {'VolRatio':<10} {'RSI':<10} {'Signal Reason':<30}\")\n            print(\"-\"*100)\n            for stock in candidates:\n                print(f\"{stock['code']:<10} {stock['name']:<15} {stock['close']:<10.2f} {stock['change']:>8.2f}% {stock['volume_ratio']:.2f} {stock['rsi']:.1f} {stock['signal_reason']}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"\\nNo candidate stocks found\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\quant_scanner_local.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":137213,"output":3142,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140355,"cost":{"input":0.08232779999999999,"output":0.0069124,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08924019999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774245572914}}
