{"type":"message","id":"c4d778a4","parentId":"387f48c4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:51:09.430Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b71e1c070a124ba089132630","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"============================================================\r\nA-Share Quant Trading - Manual Data Version\r\n============================================================\r\n\r\n[Detailed Help]\r\n\r\n[1. Add Stock Data]\r\n   Command: add\r\n   Purpose: Manually add historical price/volume data\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py add <code> <name> <date> <open> <close> <high> <low> <volume>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py add 600000 �ַ����� 2026-03-20 10.00 10.10 10.15 9.90 1000000\r\n   Note: Add multiple days by running add command multiple times\r\n         Make sure dates are in chronological order!\r\n\r\n[2. Check Buy Signal]\r\n   Command: signal\r\n   Purpose: Check if stock meets buy criteria (MA5>MA10, Volume>=1.5x, RSI<70)\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py signal <stock_code>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py signal 600000\r\n\r\n[3. Buy Stock (Add Position)]\r\n   Command: buy\r\n   Purpose: Buy stock and add to positions\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py buy <code> <name> <price> <shares>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py buy 600000 �ַ����� 10.00 500\r\n\r\n[4. Sell Position]\r\n   Command: sell\r\n   Purpose: Sell stock and remove from positions\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py sell <stock_code>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py sell 600000\r\n\r\n[5. Status Dashboard]\r\n   Command: status\r\n   Purpose: Show current positions, capital, and sell signals\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py status\r\n\r\n[Manual Data Workflow]\r\n   Since akshare/tushare are unavailable, use this manual workflow:\r\n   1. Get stock data from browser (tushare.pro, eastmoney.com)\r\n   2. Add 30-60 days of data using 'add' command\r\n   3. Check signals using 'signal' command\r\n   4. If BUY signal, buy stock using 'buy' command\r\n   5. Monitor positions using 'status' command"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2401,"aggregated":"============================================================\r\nA-Share Quant Trading - Manual Data Version\r\n============================================================\r\n\r\n[Detailed Help]\r\n\r\n[1. Add Stock Data]\r\n   Command: add\r\n   Purpose: Manually add historical price/volume data\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py add <code> <name> <date> <open> <close> <high> <low> <volume>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py add 600000 �ַ����� 2026-03-20 10.00 10.10 10.15 9.90 1000000\r\n   Note: Add multiple days by running add command multiple times\r\n         Make sure dates are in chronological order!\r\n\r\n[2. Check Buy Signal]\r\n   Command: signal\r\n   Purpose: Check if stock meets buy criteria (MA5>MA10, Volume>=1.5x, RSI<70)\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py signal <stock_code>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py signal 600000\r\n\r\n[3. Buy Stock (Add Position)]\r\n   Command: buy\r\n   Purpose: Buy stock and add to positions\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py buy <code> <name> <price> <shares>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py buy 600000 �ַ����� 10.00 500\r\n\r\n[4. Sell Position]\r\n   Command: sell\r\n   Purpose: Sell stock and remove from positions\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py sell <stock_code>\r\n   Example: python quant_scanner_manual.py sell 600000\r\n\r\n[5. Status Dashboard]\r\n   Command: status\r\n   Purpose: Show current positions, capital, and sell signals\r\n   Format: python quant_scanner_manual.py status\r\n\r\n[Manual Data Workflow]\r\n   Since akshare/tushare are unavailable, use this manual workflow:\r\n   1. Get stock data from browser (tushare.pro, eastmoney.com)\r\n   2. Add 30-60 days of data using 'add' command\r\n   3. Check signals using 'sig